00:53:36.080 --> 00:53:39.170
That was the title
of the special issue.

00:53:39.170 --> 00:53:42.850
When the section,
rather, when the committee

00:53:42.850 --> 00:53:48.640
on applied ethnomusicology was
established by SEM in 1997,

00:53:48.640 --> 00:53:52.150
Doris Dian [assumed
spelling] and Martha Davis,

00:53:52.150 --> 00:53:56.040
whose established it, chose the
term, applied ethnomusicology.

00:53:56.040 --> 00:53:59.650
ICTM, the successors

00:53:59.650 --> 00:54:01.650
of the International
Folk Music Council,

00:54:01.650 --> 00:54:03.650
the International Council
and Traditional Music,

00:54:03.650 --> 00:54:07.240
a UNESCO organization,
established a study group

00:54:07.240 --> 00:54:09.750
on applied ethnomusicology
a year or two later,

00:54:09.750 --> 00:54:12.760
I think, in 1998 or so.

00:54:12.760 --> 00:54:18.160
And so, that's the
name that's in use now.

00:54:18.160 --> 00:54:23.090
But I think it's open for
discussion, and it may be

00:54:23.090 --> 00:54:28.110
that public ethnomusicology
turns out to be a better term.

00:54:28.110 --> 00:54:30.630
There are certainly
some advantages

00:54:30.630 --> 00:54:34.370
to it emphasizes the work
in the public sphere.

00:54:34.370 --> 00:54:38.930
The problem I see with it is
that it also can be confused

00:54:38.930 --> 00:54:45.840
as a place of employment, and I
think that it's very problematic

00:54:45.840 --> 00:54:48.850
to dichotomize the academic.

00:54:48.850 --> 00:54:50.610
Obviously, I have a bias here.

00:54:50.610 --> 00:54:56.450
I think it's very problematic
to oppose the academic world

00:54:56.450 --> 00:54:58.070
and the world outside.

00:54:58.070 --> 00:55:01.340
I don't think it does
good for any -- either.

00:55:01.340 --> 00:55:05.340
And so, I see that is a
problem with the word public,

00:55:05.340 --> 00:55:09.120
but I think it certainly open,
and these things change, too,

00:55:09.120 --> 00:55:11.160
over time, and may be
in five or 10 years,

00:55:11.160 --> 00:55:12.670
public will become
the accepted word.

00:55:12.670 --> 00:55:14.970
I don't know.

